# Filling the null values in the age columns with random values within one standard deviation of the mean. This approach introduces some randomness but preserves the overall distribution.
random_ages = np.random.randint(mean_age - std_age, mean_age + std_age, size=df['Age'].isnull().sum())
In [170]:

In [186]:
# Outlier removal using Z-Score test
from scipy import stats
z_scores_age = np.abs(stats.zscore(df['Age']))
z_scores_fare = np.abs(stats.zscore(df['Fare']))
threshold = 3
outliers_age = z_scores_age > threshold
outliers_fare = z_scores_fare > threshold
median_age = df['Age'].median()
median_fare = df['Fare'].median()
df_clean = df.copy()  # Create a copy of the original DataFrame
df_clean.loc[outliers_age, 'Age'] = median_age
df_clean.loc[outliers_fare, 'Fare'] = median_fare
